@node future
@next "thanks"

Oooh. That's the question of the day, isn't it!

Well, I've got a few plans - main ones are as follows:

1. Support for searching on ingredients as well as categories. This will
    be tricky using the current recipe files, and I don't have the time
    to convert them all by hand. Perhaps if someone pays me to do it... :)

2. Support for other file types. I'm looking at Recipe Wizard on the PC
    for this at the moment, as it has a pretty funky file format.

3. Amendments to the category listview. I could have a funky explorer-type
    listview for the categories, so it would expand when you click on a
    category as follows:


     fish             fish
     morefish -->     morefish
                       |- recipe1
                        - recipe2
                        - recipe3


4. No recipe editing or entering. At least not yet. They're only text files
    for God's sake.

5. Any more ideas? email to adaml@tcp.net.uk!

If anyone wants to draw a funky NewIcon to go with the program, please do!
No MWB icons, though. Yuck.

@endnode

